name: Heart of the Fury

name: Flamebender's Tome
desc: An iron-bound sheaf of writing - some orcish and some in a language you don't recognize - that appears to have been passed down for generations.

desc: So it was that over the course of time, the man and the weapon seemed as one. Ashbringer became a name of legend, attributed not just to the fearsome blade but also to the relentless knight who wielded it.

name: Ancient Leaf
desc: It held on till the bitter end.

name: Nightfall Slippers
desc: Sometimes you must fall to know your true potential.

name: Pendant of the Kaldorei
desc: A shared ancestry can be a strong bond.

name: Orb of Dominion
desc: The Shadow Council orb whispers to you, filling your head with visions of unimaginable power.

desc: Dozens of tiny pockets, all containing various grades of explosives.

desc: Crystallized in the roiling magical pools of Farahlon, this dazzling gem is unparalled in power.

name: Tome of Chaos
desc: A volume of demonic incantations, filled with grotesque illustrations.

name: Zoug's Lifting Belt
desc: Approved by the Ogron Safety & Health Advisory Board, Blackfuse Company

name: Ogra'mal Snake Charming Flute
desc: Contains no acoustic cavity or holes to adjust pitch - it's just a stick with a rock on one end.

name: Rod of the One True Podlord
Varyx's Fealty Band
desc: He seems to have kept it all these years.

name: Musky Bat Fur Cloak
desc: The musk is overwhelming.

name: Tormented Skull
desc: Screams and weeping are heard faintly in the distance as you clutch the skull.

name: Luminous Relic Ring
desc: The power of this ring is familiar somehow.

name: Twinblades of the Deceiver
desc: Make examples of those foolish enough to oppose you, and the rest of their kind will grovel at your feet.

name: Twinblades of the Deceiver
desc: The end has come! Let the unravelling of this world commence!

name: Infernal Alchemist Stone
desc: Can be used for transmutations in place of a Philosopher's Stone.

name: Aluneth
desc: After many setbacks, Aegwynn finally bound the entity to an enchanted greatstaff. The task of containing Aluneth was done, but it would take the Guardian years to truly harness its power.

name: Stone of the Wilds
desc: Can be used for transmutations in place of a Philosopher's Stone.

name: Stone of the Elements
desc: Can be used for transmutations in place of a Philosopher's Stone.

name: Engine-Kicking Boots
desc: When other forms of repair have failed, there's always one last option.

name: Fel-Steamed Leather Tunic
desc: Smells of brimstone, but free of wrinkles!

name: Warmongering Gladiator's Felblood Gronnling
desc: Teaches you how to summon this mount.

name: Scaleshard
desc: Here is whence true strength comes. From deep places... within the world, and within oneself.

name: Scale of the Earth-Warder
desc: ...it was one of Neltharion's cast-off scales. It saved Magnar's life. The blast of flame parted around the black scale, but the sheer force carried Magnar out of the lair, sending him tumbling down the slopes of Highmountain.

name: Blades of the Fallen Prince
desc: When my days have come to an end, you shall be king.

name: Blades of the Fallen Prince
desc: I will show you the justice of the grave... and the true meaning of fear.

name: G'Hanir, the Mother Tree
desc: At the beginning, there was a source of healing and balance, a place where all life could rest and revive.

name: Maw of the Damned
desc: The Maw's thirst is unquenchable. If it is not fed fresh victims, it will not hesitate to drink from its wielder instead.

name: Apocalypse
desc: It shall sow destruction and war. Famine and death. It shall tempt with power, and then bring an end to all life.

name: Soul Remnant
desc: Trapped spirits swirl within this fractured crystal.

name: Soul Remnant
desc: Trapped spirits swirl within this fractured crystal.

name: Soul Remnant
desc: Trapped spirits swirl within this fractured crystal.

name: Fel Essence
desc: A sickly green light pulses with a hint of malevolent life.

name: Fel Essence
desc: A sickly green light pulses with a hint of malevolent life.

name: Fel Essence
desc: A sickly green light pulses with a hint of malevolent life.

name: Fangs of the Devourer
desc: The hound's bite lingers, even long after its death. A surprisingly effective and subtle tool for something so crude.

name: Fangs of the Devourer
desc: Azhir manari kirel. Akim manari galar!

name: Draenic Sea Chart
desc: A map of Draenor's seas painstakingly covered in arcane sigils and navigational information.

name: Talonclaw
desc: The Eagle Spear. Spear of the Wild Gods. Talonclaw. Bearing many names and many blessings, this is a weapon of legends.

name: Doomhammer
desc: A stranger will raise the hammer high, and with it justice shall reign.

name: Felo'melorn
desc: ...not elven weapons. Not when they are reforged with magic, and hatred, and a burning need for revenge. No, Arthas. Felo'melorn is stronger than ever-as am I. - Kael'thas Sunstrider

name: Claws of Ursoc
desc: Ursoc, brother of Ursol and guardian of the furbolg tribes... bearer of the strength of the forest itself.

name: Claws of Ursoc
desc: Azeroth will need you. If you do not stand ready, the world may fall.

name: The Silver Hand
desc: Tyr replied that he did not consider his argent hand a reminder of defeat. For him it was a symbol of the sacrifice he had made to defend Azeroth, and he wanted the world to see it that way as well.

name: Tome of the Silver Hand
desc: Esarus thar no'Darador.

name: T'uure, Beacon of the Naaru
desc: Blessed are the torchbearers, who bring light to the darkness.

name: Thas'dorah, Legacy of the Windrunners
desc: When it was retrieved from the Sunwell, the bow radiated power. Talanas was humbled by the gift. He named the weapon Thas'dorah, \Valor of the Forest.\""

name: Xal'atath, Blade of the Black Empire
desc: Xal'atath has a mind of its own. Ignore its maddening whispers. Do not trust the lies it spins. Take from it what you need, but always remember that the dark presence in the blade is not your ally.

name: Aldrachi Warblades
desc: His warblades howled over the clamor of battle, rending anything that came near. Each demon Toranaar vanquished seemed to fill him with renewed vigor and strength. He was an army unto himself.

name: Aldrachi Warblades
desc: The Aldrachi were a proud race. Too proud to serve. Millions of demons died before the Aldrachi were wiped out, and it took Sargeras himself to kill their king.

name: Scythe of Elune
desc: There is power within that would be freed. With balance and control, the wolf may be tamed, but only for a time.

name: Fangs of Ashamane
desc: She ripped through the demons' ranks and then disappeared into the trees. She crept along the high branches and dove down upon the Legion commanders. She was a terror, a fearsome beast, and she held nothing back, offering no mercy.

name: Fangs of Ashamane
desc: The sacrifice of Ashamane is remembered to this day. We live by her grace, and her children still tread the forests with us as our closest companions.

name: Titanstrike
desc: A peerless example of techno-magical engineering, infused with the power of storms.

name: Ebonchill
desc: Ebonchill contained only a sliver of Alodi's might, but even that was more than most magi could ever hope of wielding.

name: Truthguard
desc: With the first hammer fall, rivers of magma spilled from the icy mountains. With the second, the sky howled and lightning set the heavens aflame. With the third, a single ray of sunlight pierced the storm clouds and whispered over Truthguard's surface.

name: Oathseeker
desc: Killing for the sake of killing... conquering for the sake of conquest... there is no honor in such things. There is only shame and regret.

name: Light's Wrath
desc: It was with our greatest hopes and prayers that we attended the ceremony that day... and it is with our greatest sorrows that we departed it.

name: The Kingslayers
desc: It was not a pleasant death. But it was fast, quiet, and efficient. When the orc took his last breath, the wound that killed him became irregular. Nobody would be able to tell whether he had died to a knife, an axe, or a spear.

name: The Kingslayers
desc: Countless voices hushed, and countless leaders toppled... all at the whim of his foul command. There would be no redemption for these acts, only solitude and sorrow.

name: The Dreadblades
desc: She saw herself commanding an impossibly large pirate fleet, one that could conquer the high seas and all the nations of Azeroth. Every ship that dared to challenge her burned, and every city gave up its treasures or was destroyed.

name: Fury of the Stonemother
desc: Created through the power of Doomhammer and the powerful shaman who wields it.

name: Warswords of the Valarjar
desc: Helya's betrayal shall never be forgiven. Let her rot beneath the waves, far from the Halls of Valor.

name: Strom'kar, the Warbreaker
desc: The steel of the barbarian king shall strike the final blow. It shall silence the din of battle, and bring the first kingdom into an age of peace.

name: Sharas'dal, Scepter of Tides
desc: They drifted into the abyss, but Azshara and her Highborne remained unbroken. The darkness around them was absolute, and so the queen willed Sharas'dal to bring them light...

name: Shield of the Sea Queen
desc: As the ocean crushed the life from their bodies, ancient creatures stirred in the darkness. Their whispers flowed through the currents. Their powers wrapped tight around the queen and her servants.

name: The Fist of Ra-den
desc: To seal Al'Akir's demise, Master Ra slammed his fist into the mountaintop. The heavens split wide, and all the fire and fury they contained crashed down atop the Windlord's head.

name: The Highkeeper's Ward
desc: Ra and Helya crafted a shield, the Highkeeper's Ward, to act as a key to the Elemental Plane. It thrummed with the energies of the four elements, which Ra could call upon whenever he desired.

name: Sheilun, Staff of the Mists
desc: You seek the calm, inevitable force of a deep river, the kind that carves canyons into the toughest stone and carries away warriors on its currents without so much as a ripple. Sheilun is the embodiment of that idea.

name: Fu Zan, the Wanderer's Companion
desc: From the beginning, this staff has accompanied legendary creatures and immortal spirits as they carried out important, lasting work all across Azeroth.

name: Fists of the Heavens
desc: When Irmaat hefted his two weapons and tested the power within them, uncontrollable fury spilled forth.

name: Scepter of Sargeras
desc: When at last the moment arrived for Ner'zhul to act, he did so with wild abandon, heedless of the consequences. It mattered not to him if Draenor was destroyed; in fact, he welcomed it as part of his legacy.

name: Ulthalesh, the Deadwind Harvester
desc: The scythe's master will either overcome Sataiel or be consumed, which will only make the blade more powerful. And then another bearer will take their place. And another.

name: Skull of the Man'ari
desc: When finally Thal'kiel emerged, he was changed. He had aged by centuries, alone in the dark with his thoughts and his thralls. His back was twisted and stooped, and there was an odd glimmer in his eye. He summoned his Wakeners, and we answered the call...

name: The Houndmaster's Fancy Pants
desc: One must dress in style for the hunt.

name: Scale Helm of the Frigid Depths
Arcanetic Plate Greaves
desc: A mysterious arcane force binds these plates tightly together.

name: Ring of the Dread Pirate Bob
The Violaceous Pearl
desc: Mrrgrl claimed this from Troggl, who stole it from Ruggrr, who killed Purgg for it, who...

name: Bitterbrine's Signet Ring
desc: Bitterbrine's ring is one of a kind amongst the Gilblin of the Broken Isles.

name: Sssurine's Luxurious Sssandals
desc: A lady of the high court doesn't throw away good shoes, for any reason.

name: Bile-Resistant Boots
desc: While Bilebrain's many experiments have not been successful, his boots are surprisingly impervious to bile.

name: Daggerbeak's Nesting Legguards
desc: Twigs and bits of straw are stuck in the ringmail.

name: Bosun's Acid-Blotched Cape
desc: Flog didn't care if they were actually captains.

name: Brvet's Hauberk of Command
desc: Addorned with the captain's various commisions that were later copied by other captains.

name: The Hammer's Head
desc: Forged from the scraps of her shields the metal links are as strong as any shield.

name: Trader's Band
desc: The mark of an 'honest' merchant.

name: Tideskorn Jarl's Pendant
desc: The badge of the current Jarl of the Tideskorn.

name: Andvari's Gift
desc: A glint of gold escapes the ring's stench of death.

name: Stormslayer Champion Belt
desc: Decorated with the scales of numerous storm drakes.

name: Wyrmy Tunkins
desc: NYI - Pet

name: Flamescale Mail
desc: Usually quenched by the sea.

name: Da Basher's Toy Armor
desc: Only a few chunks of the toy remain inside.

name: Void Slippers
desc: Your feet are caressed in shadows.

name: Plate Hiking Boots
desc: Only redeeming quality... very durable.

name: Spine of Barax
desc: Every hunter loves a trophy.

name: Guile of the Hold's Sky Terrors
Pillars of the Dark Portal
desc: Corrupted by the demonlord Sargeras, Medivh contacted the orc warlock Gul'dan and together they opened the Dark Portal, allowing the Burning Legion to begin its invasion of Azeroth.

name: Shackles of Bryndaor
desc: For his misdeeds, Bryndaor was charged with guarding the gates of Helheim for eternity.

name: Koltira's Newfound Will
desc: Following the Battle for Light's Hope Chapel, the two comrades parted ways. Thassarian opted to serve his king, while Koltira, former defender of Quel'Thalas, chose to join his people, the blood elves.

name: Service of Gorefiend
desc: After his demise, Gorefiend returned as the first death knight and swore allegiance to Orgrim Doomhammer.

name: Wilfred's Sigil of Superior Summoning
desc: Left at home on a crucial day during the Argent Tournament.

name: Kazzak's Final Curse
desc: As the Doom Lord crossed through the Dark Portal to Outland, he left his enemies with a parting gift...

name: Odr, Shawl of the Ymirjar
desc: Found pristine under burnt rubble in the village of Ymirheim.

name: Acherus Drapes
desc: For you do not face me alone, but the host of the Ebon Blade itself. We are undying, we are unceasing, and we hunger for life!

name: Sacrolash's Dark Strike
desc: Misery... confusion... mistrust. These are the hallmarks.

name: Sin'dorei Spite
desc: So many of our people have been twisted and dominated by the Burning Legion. It's only fitting that we in turn use their own armies against them.

name: Streten's Sleepless Shackles
desc: The only risk is that you'll go insane.

name: Recurrent Ritual
desc: It was always a wonder to outsiders how certain Vrykul warlocks managed to summon and command enormous packs of felstalkers.

name: Hood of Eternal Disdain
desc: Whoever dons this hood gains unholy strength and resolve, but will forever lose all kindness and compassion. Beware...

name: Marquee Bindings of the Sun King
desc: Contrary to popular belief, Kael'thas's favored, and usually final, utterance to his enemies was actually 'PYROBLAST!'.

name: Magistrike Restraints
desc: Varo'then was madly in love with the queen. Unfortunately, he never had the opportunity to use these restraints on her.

name: Anund's Seared Shackles
desc: Why Anund was standing in front of Kaldrigos is anyone's guess. However, legend has it that Anund's final Shadow Word: Pain was key in helping Korl defeat the dread wyrm.

name: Shard of the Exodar
desc: The draenei capital city is able to transcend dimensions and even warp time itself. What could a sliver of its power do in the hands of a mere mortal?

name: Lady Vashj's Grasp
desc: Imbued with the power of the naga sea witch, your fingers inside feel frigid but surprisingly limber and highly energized.

name: Rhonin's Assaulting Armwraps
desc: Mages who wield as much power as Rhonin, a former leader of the Kirin Tor, often use arcane bindings to steady the magic unleashing from their fingertips.

name: Skjoldr, Sanctuary of Ivagont
desc: Ivagont fought at Kakushan's side, as he always does, during their massacre of the Stormscale naga in Darkshore. By virtue of his protection, they left unscathed.

name: Mother Shahraz's Seduction
desc: You seem a little tense...

name: Draugr, Girdle of the Everlasting King
desc: Legend holds that the bodies of the titanspawn are so saturated with the energy of the creators that they leave behind fragments when the mortal host dies. This girdle is said to have been painstakingly sewn together from those fragments.

name: Cord of Infinity
desc: The magic contained inside seems to be as endless as the Burning Legion.

name: Aggramar's Stride
desc: Time and space are one. To a watcher of the universe, distance is nearly meaningless.

name: Prydaz, Xavaric's Magnum Opus
desc: Bearers of this amulet whistle a haunting tune, and those nearby attest to a distant cry of anguish between the notes.

name: Al'maiesh, the Cord of Hope
desc: It is said that this once belonged to the original Val'kyr.

name: Entrancing Trousers of An'juna
desc: Bearers of these trousers often go above and beyond the call of duty.

name: The Instructor's Fourth Lesson
desc: Thought to be given by Razuvious to his most gifted acolytes, it is unclear how this band escaped the walls of Naxxramas. Could the Lich King have sent his own agents to the Broken Isles?

name: Phyrix's Embrace
desc: Phyrix was a legendary priest who led adventurers through Molten Core and Blackwing Lair. She met an unfortunate demise at the hands of Nefarian, but her spirit still protects Azeroth's champions to this day.

name: Muze's Unwavering Will
desc: From their humble beginnings in Silvermoon to the depths of Blackrock Mountain, Muze always remained steadfast, faithfully healing her companions and saving them from the brinks of death.

name: Mystic Kilt of the Rune Master
desc: While Northrend's half-giants naturally know little to no magic, the mystic vrykul of Stormheim are masters of rune magic.

name: Sephuz's Secret
desc: Intangibility is a curious concept. The word suggests some magical ability, but in the physical world, it simply means the power to be here or there, now or later.

name: Rattlegore Bone Legplates
desc: Parts of the shambling horror Rattlegore still contain potent necromantic energies that respond to the will of those strong enough to command them.

name: Koralon's Burning Touch
desc: Deep within the vault protected by Wintergrasp, Koralon the Flame Watcher was furious when intruders entered.

name: Norgannon's Foresight
desc: Magic must be regulated, managed, and controlled. But it must also be appreciated and valued, not hoarded. Such is the paradox that you must comprehend.

name: Feretory of Souls
desc: Viewed from different angles, there seems to be faint reflection of three different faces.

name: Power Cord of Lethtendris
desc: Lethtendris constructed a device to siphon Dire Maul's overwhelming corrupt power for herself.

name: Toravon's Whiteout Bindings
desc: Deep within the vault protected by Wintergrasp, Toravon the Ice Watcher was relentless in smashing interlopers.

name: Perseverance of the Ebon Martyr
desc: Cold steel rests heavily on the brow of this crown's bearer.

name: Alythess's Pyrogenics
desc: Depravity... hatred... chaos. These are the pillars.

name: Xalan the Feared's Clench
desc: Ripped from Xalan's hands by night elves during the War of the Satyr.

name: Roots of Shaladrassil
desc: The ties of the earth are deep, consistent, and rarely waver.

name: Estel, Dejahna's Inspiration
desc: Faith is the beginning of all things. If your skill with the arcane is passable, but not strong, you may still become a sorceress. But if your faith is only passable and not strong, you will never become a priestess.

name: Darckli's Dragonfire Diadem
desc: Among Archmage Darckli's innumerable achievements was mastering the art of breathing dragonfire directly from his mouth.

name: Mangaza's Madness
desc: Mangaza of the Kaldorei was innovative among his brethen for his dedication to a different form of magic, choosing to assault the mind over the body. Tragically, this method eventually proved maddening to himself in addition to his victims.

name: Buccaneer's Lucky Chain
desc: It has been gathering new luck since the giants 'procured' it.

name: Talisman of the Lost Blue Flight
Soul Fragment of a Faronaar Innocent
Intro to Fel Magic - Pocket Edition
Dathrohan's Signet
desc: It wasn't hard to corrupt one of those crusaders.

name: 'Procured' Kirin Tor Wand Tip
desc: The wand was broken already...

name: Rare White Tiger Heart
desc: I didn't ask Nessingwary any questions.

name: Fel-Fire Demon Claw
desc: Collected this one myself.

name: Sorceror's Ember
desc: Would you try and touch it with your hand?

name: Were-Yeti Paw
desc: He transformed right before my eyes!

name: Myzrael Shard
desc: My contact in Arathi said it was powerful, but it looks like a rock.

name: Ravenous Seed
desc: What kind of plant can bite before it is even planted?

name: Zandalari Voodoo Totem
desc: The guy claimed he actually got it on Zandalar, shortly before he died from a strange disease.

name: Breath of Al'Akir
desc: When we found our collector he was stuck in a tree in Un'goro.

name: Croc-Resistant Waders
desc: Original Nessingwary Issue

name: Muck-Covered Shoes
desc: Fresh out of a mud-lined crate, who knows what lies under the muck.

name: Grasping Tentacle Loop
desc: Nearly impossible to remove once it latches on.

name: Horn of Valor
desc: The strongest Vrykul are awaited by Odyn at the Halls of Valor, to become Valarjar. They fight eternal, shiny and gold.

name: Cord of Maiev, Priestess of the Moon
desc: In a life long forgotten, Maiev, Hunter of the Betrayer, healed the injured and worshipped the moon goddess.

name: Fists of the Heavens
desc: There was a great flash of light and a great rush of air, and when it was done, Irmaat could feel his weapons, Al'burq and Alra'ed trembling with elemental power.

name: Secrets of the Void
desc: The moment I touched the blade, a name was spoken in my mind: Xal'atath. I knew then that I could not destroy the dagger. Not yet. How can one defeat a power she does not understand?

name: Heart of the Phoenix
desc: When the fighting was done, Dath'Remar stood painted in demon blood. As night fell, we knew that more battles remained, and yet, with this elf and this blade among us, we held out hope that victory did not lie beyond our grasp.

name: Zann'esu Journey
desc: The Zann'esu mage clan left their home village of Brunnhildar in search of the perfect magic to defeat the Lich King. They never returned.

name: Zenk'aram, Iridi's Anadem
desc: Constructed from the finest felcloth, Iridi drew power from this anadem to defeat Dargonax.

name: The Twins' Painful Touch
desc: 'Enough with these orbs, Fjola. Let's finish these challengers.' -Eydis Darkbane

name: Lana'thel's Lament
desc: Lana'thel shed tears for the lives of the elven kin she expected to lose during their war march to Northrend. She had no idea at the time that she would be the cause of many more.

name: Cinidaria, the Symbiote
desc: This demonic symbiote adapted to draw power from the thrill of combat, sometimes mimicking the actions of its host.

name: Belo'vir's Final Stand
desc: The final act of Belo'vir Salonar, grand magister of Quel'Thalas during the Third War, was to teleport Lady Liadrin to safety as the city fell.

name: Drained Mana Crystal
desc: No more mana, but still packs a wallop.

name: Glinting Quartz Ring
desc: It looks more magical than it is.

name: Braided Silver Ring
desc: The name 'Brandy' is engraved on the inside.

name: The Dreadblades
desc: No blade can shed the blood of so many innocents and not demand a toll on its wielder as well. They are no treasure.

name: Warswords of the Valarjar
desc: In truth, it is her power that makes these weapons truly magnificent. Her power, laced with her hatred, crashes endlessly against Odyn's spirit. The tension between those energies will forever permeate these blades...

name: Fel-Touched Crate of Battlefield Goods
desc: May contain a piece of equipment.

name: Corrupted G'Hanir, the Mother Tree
desc: The power of this artifact has been diminished by the corruption deep within.

name: Vindictive Gladiator's Drape of the Tracker
Vindictive Gladiator's Drape of the Tracker
Vindictive Combatant's Drape of the Tracker
Vindictive Combatant's Drape of the Tracker
Vindictive Gladiator's Drape of the Tracker
Vindictive Gladiator's Drape of the Tracker
Archmage Karlain's Imbued Silkweave Robe
desc: A beautifully-embroidered cloth robe. It would be quite a shame if it were to be thrown into a demonic furnace...

name: Battle Mace of the Horde Vanguard
Doomhammer Offhand Appearance Record (referenced by actual item)
Felgibber Shotgun
desc: Sold by Engineering vendors in Dalaran.

name: \Twirling Bottom\" Repeater"
desc: Who knew that the term \Twisting Nether\" was copyrighted? Sold by Engineering vendors in Dalaran."

name: Surface-to-Infernal Rocket Launcher
desc: Sold by Engineering vendors in Dalaran.

name: Chaos Blaster
desc: Sold by Engineering vendors in Dalaran.

name: Amalgam's Seventh Spine
desc: This oversized bone is slowly leaking soul energy.

name: Snapped Emerald Pendant
desc: Predating the War of the Ancients, exquisite craftsmanship distracts from a dangerous secret.

name: Cushioned Treads of Glory
desc: Long vigils require soft shoes.

name: Empowered Soul Shard
desc: It does not reflect the face of the viewer, but rather the face of the soul trapped within.

name: Darkened T'uure
desc: This artifact has fallen to darkness.

name: Achor, the Eternal Hunger
desc: Demon hunters possess a thirst for battle as endless as the legions of their most hated enemy.

name: Ekowraith, Creator of Worlds
desc: We could not only evoke, but conjure a place of our own. And that everywhere... that has ever existed... it was all in service of our dream. Now please... Hear what I hear.

name: Sal'salabim's Lost Tunic
desc: Sal'salabim might have lost this when he blacked out for 6 hours...

name: Breastplate of the Golden Val'kyr
desc: The remnant of a great commander who descended upon her enemies from the heavens, shining with the radiance of the sun.

name: Destiny Driver
desc: Bend time itself to protect the world from devastation.

name: Cenedril, Reflector of Hatred
desc: If you know the enemy and know yourself, you need not fear the result of a hundred battles.

name: Whisper of the Nathrezim
desc: Pitiful... Is that the best you can do?

name: The Dreadlord's Deceit
desc: I've been preparing for you, young prince. I am Mal'Ganis. As you can see, your people are now mine...

name: Loramus Thalipedes' Sacrifice
desc: These boots are the only thing that remained after the Stone Knife of Sealing trapped Rakh'likh within Loramus the Defiled's body.

name: Promise of Elune, the Moon Goddess
desc: When others receive life and energy from you, you too shall receive life and energy from me.

name: Ailuro Pouncers
desc: The madness within Marl Wormthorn is said to have empowered these boots.

name: Skysec's Hold
desc: During the Battle for Mount Hyjal, Skysec, guardian of Nordrassil, endured endless waves of scourge and legion. In the end, he proudly gave his life in defense of the ancient world tree.

name: Essence of Infusion
desc: Feel nature flowing through your veins.

name: Firestone Walkers
desc: 'Brother Adam and Brother David were brilliant mathematicians and monks, always blabbing about abacuses and parabolas.' -Brynild the Brewmaster

name: Ei'thas, Lunar Glides of Eramas
desc: Eramas Brightblaze always remarked how comfortable these were.

name: Katsuo's Eclipse
desc: Said Kaulder to his brother Katsuo: 'With training, your reactions can become faster and your fists can become more furious than any foe can handle.'

name: Duskwalker's Footpads
desc: If an SI:7 agent like Caelvana has you in her sights, you'd better run. You better run far, and you better do it quickly.

name: Thraxi's Tricksy Treads
desc: Thraxi often disguised herself as a brewmaster monk to deceive her enemies.

name: Shadow Satyr's Walk
desc: While the exact origins of the Shadow satyr are unidentified, they are known to be incorporeal creatures that not only exist inside the Emerald Nightmare but in places on Azeroth as well.

name: Ullr's Feather Snowshoes
desc: They provided the huntress with a feeling of weightlessness- a calm and serenity amid the storm.

name: Nesingwary's Trapping Treads
desc: Something with very large teeth tried taking a bite out of these boots.

name: The Deceiver's Blood Pact
desc: Ner'zhul, Elder Shaman of the Shadowmoon Clan, wanted to save his people and finally obtain the power and respect he so dearly desired. But he was deceived...

name: Elemental Rebalancers
desc: Originally used by a powerful doomguard to rain down fiery death, these were repurposed for a more benevolent cause in order to balance out the destruction they had previously caused.

name: Uvanimor, the Unbeautiful
desc: The corrupting power of the Nightwell flows through this ring, allowing the wielder to siphon power from those under their command.

name: Anger of the Half-Giants
desc: Those oversized Vrykul are not the first thing you want to run into in Northrend. Try the undead of Borean Tundra instead.

name: Impeccable Fel Essence
desc: The druids of the Emerald Circle manipulated the fel energy within this stone to enhance their attunement with the wild.

name: Chatoyant Signet
desc: The fire within Leyara enchants this signet. You can feel that she has finally found peace.

name: Dual Determination
desc: Druids of the Claw have the ability to transform, becoming either faster or tougher. They typically choose the latter.

name: Tearstone of Elune
desc: The myth surrounding Elune, one of the few true deities of Azeroth, suggest her true identity might not yet have been fully understood.

name: Frizzo's Fingertrap
desc: Apply a little butter and it comes right off!

name: Jewel of the Lost Abbey
desc: Originally a gift from the mage, Veri'thas, this trinket was allegedly stolen from the Lost Abbey after a conflict between the monks and the elves.

name: Eye of Collidus the Warp-Watcher
desc: Well... one of his eyes.

name: Ilterendi, Crown Jewel of Silvermoon
desc: Silvermoon was constructed out of radiant white stone and adorned in crimson tapestry. However, the city's renown was not merely for its beauty. Silvermoon is a seat of magical learning and home to master manipulators of mana.

name: Heathcliff's Immortality
desc: Heathcliff, known as the Immortal Object, was said to be immune to any grave injury. Some questioned whether the Blood Knight's fortitude transcended the natural laws of the world.

name: Liadrin's Fury Unleashed
desc: We were betrayed by the man we called our prince. I pledge the blades of my Blood Knights to the defeat of Kil'jaeden and the restoration of Silvermoon. We will fight beside you, A'dal.

name: Insignia of Ravenholdt
desc: An insignia only given to those who have demonstrated mastery of the shadows, and killed in service to Ravenholdt.

name: Eye of the Twisting Nether
desc: In the nether, though the elements of the world are twisted and barely recognizable, their power is without equal.

name: Focuser of Jonat, the Elder
desc: Under the training of Jonat Han, new shamans of the Dragonflayer clan mastered the ways of the waters - healing the one and the many.

name: Ayala's Stone Heart
desc: In the pits of Valhalas, Ayala the Relentless cut down foe after foe on his way to legend. Becoming more lethal as his opponents weakened, he was truly terrifying to spectate.

name: Kazzalax, Fujieda's Fury
desc: Jinyu whisper tales of the great warrior, Fujieda, who slew a mighty fel demon after lying in wait in a shallow pool for hours.

name: The Walls Fell
desc: Midst the third war, when the walls of Kalimdor defenders fell, Shaka, the Ancient of War, refused.

name: Zevrim's Hunger
desc: Its power was extracted from hunters who were sacrificed in Dire Maul.

name: Luffa Wrappings
desc: Nothing works quite like a good luffa.

name: Hidden Master's Forbidden Touch
desc: For thousands of years, ancient understandings of lifeflow manipulation have been passed in secret from one master to another.

name: Praetorian's Tidecallers
desc: Working together to defeat Azeroth's greatest enemies, the best minds congregated in a forum dedicated to intellectual discussion and war strategy while their champions battled on the frontlines.

name: Tyr's Hand of Faith
desc: After losing his hand to the massive proto-dragon Galakrond, Jotun forged Tyr a new one.

name: Archavon's Heavy Hand
desc: Deep within the vault protected by Wintergrasp, Archavon the Stone Watcher was hateful of all trespassers.

name: Raddon's Cascading Eyes
desc: As the world... goes by... we'll go on forever.

name: The Emerald Dreamcatcher
desc: Ysera dreams and the world trembles.

name: Fundamental Observation
desc: Sit back, relax, and observe the world around you.

name: The Shadow Hunter's Voodoo Mask
desc: 'If dey want to kill me, dey betta' kill me da first time. Dey betta' kill me dead. Dey betta' kill me when I'm in my sleep.' -Vol'jin, after surviving Garrosh's assassination attempt.

name: Justice Gaze
desc: This helm was once worn by Highlord Alexandros Mograine, and had things gone differently, would have been passed on to his sons, Renault and Darion Morgraine.

name: Cloak of Fel Flames
desc: Appearing like any other found in the molten depths, this one appears to burn with a greater purpose.

name: Elize's Everlasting Encasement
desc: '100% all natural fury' was an apt description of its owner during the Sundering.

name: Leggings of The Black Flame
desc: The Black Flame specializes in providing the finest services and entertainment money can buy, whether they happen to be hard to find items, gladiatorial combat, or lucrative games of chance.

name: Will of Valeera
desc: At a young age, Valeera survived the death of her parents, imprisonment, and slavery. Her enemies have always underestimated her will to survive.

name: Tyelca, Ferren Marcus's Stature
desc: Power comes from strength, and true strength comes from strong legs bolting you to the ground.

name: Runemaster's Pauldrons
desc: Molgeim of the Assembly of Iron mastered the use of runes for a myriad of devastating effects.

name: Aman'Thul's Wisdom
desc: Unto you is charged the great task of keeping the purity of time. Know that there is only one true timeline, though there are those who would have it otherwise. You must protect it.

name: Unison Spaulders
desc: Every place you've ever imagined- it is real. It is a fictional city in your mind and you know every corner of it. Your mind is a world. Each of us is a place.

name: Echoes of the Great Sundering
desc: 10,000 years ago, the Well of Eternity imploded. The effects are still felt today.

name: Tak'theritrix's Shoulderpads
desc: During the first invasion of Azeroth, legion commander Tak'theritrix was key in peeling apart the initial night elf defense.

name: Obsidian Stone Spaulders
desc: These appear to emanate the same power as the dark portal.

name: Weight of the Earth
desc: All living creatures trust in the stillness of the earth. They know nothing of the currents that flow beneath its surface. They do not comprehend its weight. They cannot understand its power.

name: The Dark Titan's Advice
desc: Patience, young one, and you someday will have it all.

name: Gai Plin's Soothing Sash
desc: Gai Plin extracted the healing powers of the Ru'shan River to infuse this belt with its soothing sensations.

name: Roar of the Seven Lions
desc: Woven from the manes of the fabled Seven Lions, this belt was crafted by the night elf sentinel Tyven.

name: War Belt of the Sentinel Army
desc: Sentinels are the expert marksmen and elite fighters among the night elves. Few warriors can match the proud archers' speed and cunning.

name: Helbrine, Rope of the Mist Marauder
desc: Ghostly howls hang in the fog long after Helheim has taken another.

name: Pristine Proto-Scale Girdle
desc: Crafted from a massive proto-dragon scale that appears ancient, yet feels still hot.

name: Akainu's Absolute Justice
desc: His molten powers could shape an entire landscape.

name: Intact Nazjatar Molting
desc: The naga of Nazjatar are masters of sorcery and natural dwellers of the ocean deeps. It makes sense that wearing their discarded skin would grant you a greater control over the tides.

name: Chain of Thrayn
desc: The prayer of an ancient Valhalas champion resonates through the links: 'If you stand in the light, you will never stand alone.'

name: Naj'entus's Vertebrae
desc: Few naga matched the strength of Naj'entus, champion of Lady Vashj and servant to Illidan Stormrage.

name: Ceann-Ar Charger
desc: Legendary fighters always take their opponents head-on.

name: Thundergod's Vigor
desc: And the god of thunder struck down transgressors with great fury and vengeance...

name: Mo'arg Bionic Stabilizers
desc: If you can stabilize a saw you can stabilize a glaive.

name: The Defiler's Lost Vambraces
desc: While in battle with Loramus Thalipedes atop the Rise of the Defiler, these vambraces flew off the wrists of Razelikh toward the Dark Portal.

name: Oneth's Intuition
desc: Aglaya would have called it Oneth's Overconfidence.

name: The Wildshaper's Clutch
desc: Twisted druids of the Wildspawn hoped to one day wield the power that Alzzin bestowed upon these.

name: Edraith, Bonds of Aglaya
desc: Crafted from the hide of an ancient bull that had been graced with a disposition of eternal happiness.

name: Petrichor Lagniappe
desc: Ah... It smells like rain today.

name: Drinking Horn Cover
desc: The hearty vrykul of Northrend were able to weather all elements if they had enough drink.

name: Zoldyck Family Training Shackles
desc: The Zoldyck family are trained from birth in the art of assassination. In the lower levels of their estate, members learn to resist the effects of and master the use of deadly poisons.

name: Greenskin's Waterlogged Wristcuffs
desc: In the lawless world of tavern brawls and spontaneous duels, accuracy is of critical importance.

name: Denial of the Half-Giants
desc: If you think a Tauren trying to hide in the shadows is laughable, you should see one of those Vrykul half-giants try to be sneaky in broad daylight!

name: Call of the Wild
desc: Hunters have a powerful connection to the wild - the ability to call upon the animal aspects to empower themselves and to befriend even the wildest of beasts.

name: Al'Akir's Acrimony
desc: Lightning still courses through these bindings. Your power feels infinite and ever increasing...

name: Storm Tempests
desc: Crafted from the scales of an ancient storm dragon, these release uncontrollable magic at everything nearby.

name: Nobundo's Redemption
desc: Farseer Nobundo left the city broken, but returned empowered by the elements.

name: Uther's Guard
desc: Uther the Lightbringer, leader of the Silver Hand, commanded such presence on the battlefield that his knights at times seemed both invincible and unstoppable.

name: Mannoroth's Bloodletting Manacles
desc: Come, feast in my blood, and soon you shall feast in the blood of your enemies.

name: Kakushan's Stormscale Gauntlets
desc: The great warrior Kakushan created these from skins of the Stormscale after he and Ivagont laid waste to their villages in Darkshore. While the naga fled in fear, the Vrykul drank the blood of their tribe members.

name: X'anshi, Shroud of Archbishop Benedictus
desc: Is it possible to succeed without any act of betrayal?

name: Shard of Nightmare
desc: The horrors within are merely a reflection of the beholder.

name: March of the Legion
desc: From his seat upon the Throne of Kil'jaeden, Doom Lord Kazzak raised his sword and called the demonic army into battle.

name: Seal of Necrofantasia
desc: Dark whispers from the Twisting Nether suggest that this seal was forged by the Nathrezim before the Third War, and given to one of the scourge's most powerful lieutenants.

name: Qa'pla, Eredun War Order
desc: With this kill, we will be the victors.

name: Spine of Thal'kiel
desc: The Wakeners' screams echoed across Argus, as a grim reminder of the price paid for dealing with demons.

name: Fragment of Xavius
desc: Obtaining this piece of Xavius's soul will surely weaken him.

name: N'ero, Band of Promises
desc: And they still feel all so wasted on myself.

name: Naraxas' Spiked Tongue
desc: This thing is enormous. It must weigh a tongue!

name: Bottled Hurricane
desc: Compressing the raging storm into a tiny flask had been accomplished by others, but keeping it cold was Stormcaller Inayad's greatest contribution to the field.

name: The Apex Predator's Claw
desc: The claw once belonged to Byakko, king of the beasts, famed companion to Wotan, the Master Hunter of the Winterskorn.

name: Infernal Writ
desc: This document is concise and exact. Brevity is the soul of writ.

name: Self-Forging Credentials
desc: These enchanted documents could probably get you into any party on the Broken Isles.

name: Ashbringer
desc: Blade of the Scarlet Highlord

name: Emalon's Charged Core
desc: Deep within the vault protected by Wintergrasp, Emalon the Storm Watcher stood guard with deadly determination.

name: Researcher's Notes
desc: A tightly bound scroll of handwritten notes.

name: The Silver Hand
desc: We never intended this path. Now... now this young world faces annihilation.

name: Truthguard
desc: This shield will shine light upon Loken's lies and treachery. Would that I could stay with you and help you fight this war.

name: Iron-Bound Crate of Battlefield Goods
desc: May contain a piece of equipment.

name: Spiritual Journey
desc: 'In order to master the wolf, you must BECOME the wolf!' -Advice of a crazed Vrykul shaman

name: Magtheridon's Banished Bracers
desc: Using a Manticron Cube occasionally renders these useless.

name: The Butcher's Apron
desc: You may wonder why he picked a red apron. Now, that is a good question.

name: The Binder's Bonds
desc: Inscribed with magical runes whose ink glows with power.

name: Pilfered Ettin String
desc: Ettin string is highly prized by condors as they require less materials for their nests.

name: Signet of Stormwind
desc: Granted to heroes of the Alliance shipping out to the battle of the Broken Shore.

name: Fortified Librarian's Grips
desc: For the real monster of books.

name: Shark-Link Gloves
desc: A fisherman friend loaned me an old set of his. For the real biters they will save a finger.

name: Bookbinding Wraps
desc: When you have to put them down, why not make use of the leather.

name: The Librarian's Handwraps
desc: Oh the days when you could wear a nice pair of gloves on the job.

name: Kul'Tiras Marine's Greaves
desc: It's suprising how common these are.

name: Standard Earthen Ring Regalia
desc: When your home base is located near a whirlpool, ships tend to lose their cargo.

name: Fragment of the Betrayer's Prison
desc: Imprisoned for ten thousand years. Banished from my own homeland. And now you dare enter MY realm? You are not prepared...

name: Ovyd's Winter Wrap
desc: The philosopher Ovyd is recounted in history as one of the few Vrykul that spurned the sword, opting instead to use the spoken word.

name: Kirel Narak
desc: Witness the flames that have consumed countless worlds. All will burn in the legion's fire!

name: Battle Mace of the Niskaran Guard
Singular Chain Leggings
desc: Try as you might, you cannot find where this series of interconnected links starts or ends.

name: Aluneth
desc: Greatstaff of the Magna

name: Pure Holy Light
desc: Remnants of pure Light collected from holy sites around Azeroth.

name: Once-Fashionable Nar'thalas Leggings
desc: Style has evolved in ten thousand years.

name: Empowered Ring of the Kirin Tor
Aluneth
desc: Greatstaff of the Magna

name: Withered Slippers
desc: It is suprising the withered don't try to eat their own clothing when it contains innate power.

name: Leyman's Boots
desc: Clearly the perils of their job caught up with them.

name: The Devilsaur's Bite
desc: Pulled from a fallen handler during a 'feeding' incident.

name: Impact Tremor
desc: Must go faster!

name: Fluctuating Arc Capacitor
desc: Capable of handling 1.21 mana sparks.

name: Trueflight Arrow
desc: Custom made for the Ranger-General, these arrows always fly true, always!

name: First Page of the Book of Shadows
desc: The texts the demons are sharing with the Felborne should be used very carefully.

name: Headpiece of the Elunian Cycle
desc: Entrusted to Priestess Tyrande since the War of the Ancients.

name: Khadgar's Pocket Warmer
desc: An ancient elemental core, useful for mundane purposes while finding the proper way to utilize its magic.

name: Prestigious Bronze Courser
desc: Teaches you how to summon this mount.

name: Prestigious Royal Courser
desc: Teaches you how to summon this mount.

name: Prestigious Forest Courser
desc: Teaches you how to summon this mount.

name: Prestigious Ivory Courser
desc: Teaches you how to summon this mount.

name: Perfect Dreamgrove Blossom
desc: The petals are all perfectly intact.

name: Prestigious Midnight Courser
desc: Teaches you how to summon this mount.

name: Prestigious Azure Courser
desc: Teaches you how to summon this mount.

name: Fel-Loaded Dice
desc: Definitely not possessed by minor demons.

name: \Borrowed\" Soul Essence"
desc: As if you have any plans of giving it back.

name: Blindside Approach
desc: The king of the hill casts the tallest shadow.

name: Pretty Silk Gloves
desc: Note attached says 'For my main squeeze, Renix.'

name: Sixtrigger Lucky Ring
desc: The brothers never leave their base without one wearing the ring.

name: Lysander's Lovindle Bracers
desc: These light chain bracers give just the right amount of protection on a midsummer's eve.

name: Royal Dagger Haft
desc: Sand trickles from a cracked glass orb in the base of the hilt.

name: Aegisjalmur, the Armguards of Awe
desc: Carved with ancient symbols of protection and invincibility, they confer dominance and a sovereign right to exist.

name: Dreadlord's Tattered Wingcover
desc: It's best to avoid examining the material too closely.

name: Scorpid Handler's Gloves
desc: Missing several fingers.

name: Ring of the Scoured Clan
desc: This ring is crudely engraved with an unmistakably Orcish symbol, but one you've never seen before.

name: Mark of Orgrimmar
desc: Granted to warriors of the Horde shipping out to the battle of the Broken Shore.

name: Essence of Clarity
desc: Shadows retreat as this fragment radiates a pure green light.

name: Essence of Clarity
desc: Shadows retreat as this fragment radiates a pure green light.

name: Essence of Clarity
desc: Shadows retreat as this fragment radiates a pure green light.

name: Shivarran Symmetry
desc: The Shivarra are thought to be three times as fanatical as most other members of the burning legion.

name: Talisman of the Shal'dorei
desc: Power radiates from this relic, allowing the bearer access to the Nighthold teleporters.

name: Talisman of the Shal'dorei
desc: Power radiates from this relic, allowing the bearer access to the Nighthold teleporters.

name: Talisman of the Shal'dorei
desc: Power radiates from this relic, allowing the bearer access to the Nighthold teleporters.

name: Magnetized Blasting Cap Launcher
desc: Small things can cause HUGE explosions!

name: Demonic Birthstone Ring
desc: Covered in hundreds of tiny fel green emeralds.

name: Ragged Azsharan Sail Fragment
desc: Tales persist of self-propelled ships in the ancient days of the elven empire.

name: Geta of Tay'Shute
desc: Each step echoes into eternity.

name: Gorrog's Serene Gaze
desc: With Lady Lightheart at his side, Gorrog could weather any storm - not even the Sundering could break their bond.

name: Fists of Thane Kray-Tan
desc: Kray-Tan led his clan to innumerable victories, his boundless strength tempered by Queen Yh'saerie's wisdom.

name: Welded Hardskin Helmet
desc: The inside is coated with a thin layer of ash.

name: Vastly Oversized Ring
desc: A symbol of status for lieutenants of Aubrdrak's massive army.

name: Six-Feather Fan
desc: Powerful enough to cool down even the mightiest beings who are caught in its breeze.

name: Queen Yh'saerie's Pendant
desc: Yh'saerie shared the mantle of rulership with Thane Kray-Tan, her judgment guiding their clan to prosperity even in times of war.

name: Talisman of Jaimil Lightheart
desc: Jaimil's unwavering faith in the Light brought Gorrog to her, and kept them safe during the Sundering.

name: Treia's Handcrafted Shroud
desc: Woven from purified starlight.

name: Cloak of Martayl Oceanstrider
desc: A souvenir of Martayl's bizarre, bungling journey.

name: Life-Giving Berries
desc: Death brings new life.

name: Rivantas' Silk Gloves
desc: Luckily, gloves two and six are in perfect condition.

name: Llorian's Dress Leggings
desc: Folded nicely, these pants are ready for one more dress occasion that probably will never come.

name: Ari's Wooden Ring
desc: A simple, smooth ring carved from heartwood. It is strangely warm to the touch.

name: Confiscated Manacles
desc: Pink and fluffy.

name: Aran's Relaxing Ruby
desc: Marked with a raven silhouette.

name: Faith's Crucible
desc: Marked with a raven silhouette.

name: Bloodstained Handkerchief
desc: Marked with a raven silhouette.

name: Mrrgria's Favor
desc: Marked with a raven silhouette.

name: Inescapable Dread
desc: Marked with a raven silhouette.

name: Fluctuating Energy
desc: Marked with a raven silhouette.

name: Toe Knee's Promise
desc: Marked with a raven silhouette.

name: Deteriorated Construct Core
desc: Marked with a raven silhouette.

name: Eye of Command
desc: Marked with a raven silhouette.

name: Majordomo's Dinner Bell
desc: Marked with a raven silhouette.

name: Raven Eidolon
desc: Marked with a raven silhouette.

name: Terestian's Signet Ring
desc: Abandoned by a previous tenant of the Menagerie.

name: Ring of Collapsing Futures
desc: Greed and foolishness will consume you.

name: Inordinately Wondrous Wristguards
desc: These positively-charged khorium bands increase energy and relaxation.

desc: Grook 'em in the jabber!

name: The Emperor's Capacitor
desc: Stolen from the Highkeeper Ra-den, the Fallen Keeper of Storms.

name: X'oni's Caress
desc: X'oni's mere presence was enough to cheer up her allies. Even though she was one of the most powerful druids to ever exist, many of her tricks were learned from the legendary priest, Phyrix.

name: Kam Xi'raff
desc: Named after a unique priest, whose name no one could utter.

name: Rammal's Ulterior Motive
desc: Verius quickly became aware of Rammal's motives once he revealed his true form.

name: Archimonde's Hatred Reborn
desc: Archimonde the Defiler, overlord of the legion army and wielder of limitless magics, has destroyed countless worlds across the infinity of the universes.

name: Velen's Future Sight
desc: Velen the Ageless One, known by his people as the Prophet, blessed with the gift of Sight, and aided by the Light, has led the draenei for over 25,000 years.

name: Kil'jaeden's Burning Wish
desc: Kil'jaeden the Deceiver, supreme commander of the Burning Legion, has a simple agenda: consume all life and magic, assimilate every race into the Legion's ranks, slay any who dare resist, and destroy all of creation.

name: Ice Time
desc: They always seem to have something magical up their sleeves.

name: Maraad's Dying Breath
desc: In the Light, we are one.

name: Gravity Spiral
desc: The existence and mixture of various forces and energies often forms powerful vortices of mana.

name: Saruan's Resolve
desc: Contrary to the lies of Matis the Cruel, Saruan remained steadfast until his departure from the Light.

name: Anvil-Hardened Wristwraps
desc: They once belonged to Wei Speedstout, master of ale and smithing.

name: Delusions of Grandeur
desc: Great power... at any cost.

name: Death March
desc: In this world, nothing is certain except death.

name: Skullflower's Haemostasis
desc: Your blood for my blood.

name: Spirit of the Darkness Flame
desc: The Dragon of the Darkness Flame can sometimes damage the wielder horribly. But when controlled, the wielder gains tremendous power.

name: Consort's Cold Core
desc: And in her dying moments... Sindragosa's final thoughts turned to bitterness, hatred, and revenge.

name: Lady and the Child
desc: Through introspection and perseverance, Archdruid Thom'acos learned to replicate the power of the twin moons.

name: MKII Gyroscopic Stabilizer
desc: Through conservation of angular momentum of course! Quite simple, really.

name: The Mantle of Command
desc: Disobedient pets end up on the mantle.

name: Shelter of Rin
desc: Rin watches over us, as Emperor Shaohao once did for her and for the rest of Pandaria.

name: Fiery Red Maimers
desc: Cats are capricious. If they walk up to you, it's great. But if you try to walk up them it doesn't always go so well.

name: Pyrotex Ignition Cloth
desc: Of course you can fight fire with fire. You can fight everything with fire.

name: Ashes to Dust
desc: Ashes... ashes... they all fall down.

name: Butcher's Bone Apron
desc: Ahhh... Fresh meat...

name: Reap and Sow
desc: If you reap what you sow... Well, I guess I better get going then.

name: Lessons of Space-Time
desc: The increase of chaos is what distinguishes the past from the future, giving a direction to time. -Hawking, Professor of Space-Time

name: Wakener's Loyalty
desc: Thal'kiel was a sorcerer of unmatched talent who led an order of eredar magi called the Wakeners, specialists in the arts of conjuration and binding. This is a symbol of their loyalty even after death.

name: Cloak of Multitudinous Sheaths
desc: If you've ever wanted to carry dozens of knives easily, you're in luck.

name: Fashionable Autumn Cloak
desc: Do not wear in the spring months, lest you be ridiculed.

name: Oakheart's Puny Quods
desc: My bark is worse than my bite...

name: Zeks Exterminatus
desc: You think I'm scared of death? I've done it a million times. I'm great at it. How many times have you died?

desc: Can be used for transmutations in place of a Philosopher's Stone.

name: Soul of the Archdruid
desc: The Cenarion Circle reside in the Dreamgrove. They are the guardians of nature, the preservers of balance, and the protectors of all life.

name: Soul of the Slayer
desc: The Illidari reside in the Fel Hammer. They wield the forbidden powers of the demons they slay to fight the forces of chaos - at any cost.

name: Soul of the Deathlord
desc: The Knights of the Ebon Blade reside in Acherus, the Ebon Hold. They were once the champions of the scourge. They are now the damned.

name: Soul of the Huntmaster
desc: The Unseen Path reside in the Trueshot Lodge. They are the watchers in the wild. They are the eagle on the wind. They walk the lonely road.

name: Soul of the Archmage
desc: The Tirisgarde reside in the Hall of the Guardian. They are the elite mage-guard of Dalaran, called upon in the past by the Council of Tirisfal to do battle in the absence of the Guardian.

name: Soul of the Grandmaster
desc: The Order of the Broken Temple reside in the Temple of the Five Dawns. They are the bringers of hope to a dim future.

name: Soul of the Highlord
desc: The Order of the Silver Hand reside in the Sanctum of Light. They are the united might of the Argent Crusade, the Hand of Argus, the Sunwalkers, and the Blood Knights.

name: Soul of the High Priest
desc: The Conclave reside in the Netherlight Temple. They are the masters of the Light and embracers of the Void - for light cannot exist without darkness, and darkness without light.

name: Soul of the Farseer
desc: The Earthen Ring reside in the Heart of Azeroth. They wield the power of the elemental forces between which they maintain balance. They are the true masters of the elements.

name: Soul of the Netherlord
desc: The Council of the Black Harvest reside in the Dreadscar Rift. They are the takers of souls, the commanders of demons, and the masters of the dark arts.

name: Soul of the Battlelord
desc: The Valarjar reside in the Skyhold. They are the mighty ascended champions of Odyn who protect the world from all threats.

name: The Topless Tower
desc: In the room the men have come and gone, / Talking of Alleria and Turalyon.

name: Chameleon Song
desc: The Keepers maintained peace with the knowledge that nothing endures: not a tree, not love, not even a death by violence.

name: Doorway to Nowhere
desc: Two paths diverged in the mist, and I... / I took the third, untraveled by.

name: Fire in the Deep
desc: And the wrath of the demons would challenge their worth; / And the idols were broke in the shrine of the Earth.

name: Inner Hallation
desc: Lend me your power, and immortality will be ours.

name: The Alabaster Lady
desc: When the stars threw down their spears / And water'd heaven with their tears: / Did she smile her work to see?

name: Stormstout's Last Gasp
desc: Why do we fight? To protect home and family... To preserve balance and bring harmony.

name: Soulflayer's Corruption
desc: The origins of the Soulflayer remain unknown. There are no mentions of him in any of the Titan records.

name: Cold Heart
desc: The beating of a frozen heart can be heard from a vast distance away, reminding all living things of their inevitable death.

name: Chaos Theory
desc: Within chaos there exists repetition, feedback loops, and underlying patterns.

name: Oblivion's Embrace
desc: There is no better guide to the world than oblivion.

name: Radiant Moonlight
desc:
Doubt thou the stars are fire;
Doubt that the sun doth move.

name: Behemoth Headdress
desc: Don't wake a tiger from its nap.

name: Fury of Nature
desc: Harmony between the natural and supernatural forces may be difficult to achieve, but leads to substantial greatness.

name: Celerity of the Windrunners
desc: 'Your heart flew straight as any arrow upon the wind, sister. You were the brightest of our Order. You were the most beloved of our kin.' -Sylvanas, to Alleria.

name: Parsel's Tongue
desc: A rare power usually belonging to those with an affinity for serpents.

name: Unseen Predator's Cloak
desc: Even the most powerful enemy has a weakness that can be exposed.

name: Mantle of the First Kirin Tor
desc: Thousands of years ago, the high elves of Quel'Thalas taught the arcane arts to the humans, who went on to form the Kirin Tor and rule over Dalaran.

name: Contained Infernal Core
desc: The Infernal Core frequently erupts with jets of flame that burn with enough heat to melt through the toughest of materials.

name: Shattered Fragments of Sindragosa
desc: Forged from the remnants of Arthas' destruction at Sindragosa's Fall, this sends a chill down the wearer's spine.

name: The Wind Blows
desc: The sun rises, the wind blows, and the mighty fall.

name: Pillars of Inmost Light
desc: The light shines brightest in those it consumes.

name: Scarlet Inquisitor's Expurgation
desc: Can you not see it, brothers and sisters? There is but one way to wipe the Scourge from the face of Azeroth.

name: Heart of the Void
desc: The Void is not empty. It is full of malice, despair, and death.

name: The Empty Crown
desc: It's hard to put a leash on a dog once you've put a crown on its head.

name: The Curse of Restlessness
desc: We get restless easily. We need something to do.

name: The First of the Dead
desc: Death comes to us all in the end...

name: Smoldering Heart
desc: The essence of thousands of fiery elementals have been imbued in these gloves, yet they are strangely cool to the touch.

name: The Master Harvester
desc: Out of suffering emerges the strongest of souls.

name: Ararat's Bloodmirror
desc: His blood infuses the glimmering steel, spilled by dragons, gods, and demons. Even from beyond, he protects his friends.

name: The Great Storm's Eye
desc: In the eye of the tornado, there's no high and low, no floor and sky.

name: Valarjar Berserkers
desc: They aren't known for their subtlety.

name: Tarratus Keystone
desc: A prison world for rebellious demons, the radiance of Tarratus' sun is breathtaking to behold.

name: Cavalier Hat of the Dashing Scoundrel
